		<div><br /> Sure the stuns save damage.<br />
Only problem it doesn't matter, because complete heal is a low lvl spell and is way too powerfull.<br />
Stuns are only usefull, when you don't have a cleric in the group and have to rely on slower and lower heal spells.<br />
It's more effective for the &quot;group mana&quot;, that the wizard just nukes and the cleric just heals. You prevent almost the identical damage, by just nuking anyway.<br />
<br />
It's sad, but the game is imbalanced on the healing part, too bad it can't be fixed, because all the mob damage and so is also based on the complete heal spells that are now in the game.<br />
<br />
Stuns are so far only usefull to disrupt casters, but prevent damage? Nah, maybe in 2 percent of the situation, where the cleric is not paying attention or fizzles his complete heal.<br />
<br />
I sure wish, they were more usefull. So far i only use stuns when solo or against complete heal mobs.<br />
